    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <head>Translated parts</head>
                <p xml:id="CH1a0928-start">
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_008-28a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2021-01-29T20:01:54.907+09:00">If a family is wealthy, distant relatives flock together,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_008-28a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2021-01-29T20:02:11.37+09:00">If a family is poor, brothers become separated;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_008-28a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2021-01-29T20:04:06.458+09:00">It is not because they are not inclined towards each other,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_008-28a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2021-01-29T20:04:28.78+09:00">but because their interests are not sufficient to tolerate each other.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_008-33a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2021-01-29T20:24:46.938+09:00">If the ruler is enlightened and his subjects are morally upright,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_008-33a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2021-01-29T20:24:32.088+09:00">that is the good fortune of the land.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_008-33a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2021-01-29T20:23:21.681+09:00">If the father is paternally caring and the son filially pious,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_008-33a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2021-01-29T20:24:14.875+09:00">the husband reliable and the wife truly devoted,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_008-33a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2021-01-29T20:24:25.19+09:00">that is the good fortune of the family.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_008-33a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2021-01-29T20:59:12.341+09:00">However, Bigan was not able to preserve Yin, although he was loyally devoted,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_008-33a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2021-01-29T21:00:51.135+09:00">and Shensheng was not able to pacify Jin, although he was filially pious.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_008-33a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2021-01-29T23:02:48.547+09:00">In both these [cases] there was a loyal subject and a filially pious son, and yet the nations were destroyed and thrown into chaos,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_008-33a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2021-01-29T23:03:02.011+09:00">how is this possible?</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_008-33a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2021-01-29T23:06:25.04+09:00">There was no enlightened ruler or worthy father listening to them.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_008-33a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2021-01-29T23:13:09.591+09:00">Consequently, a filially pious son does not live in the home of a paternally caring father,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_008-33a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2021-01-29T23:13:36.604+09:00">and a loyal subject does not live beneath an ideal ruler.</seg>
                </p>
            </div>
